

##################
tail -f 
###################

troubleshooting logs - splunkd.log
	tail -f /opt/splunkforwarder/var/log/splunk/splunkd.log

	tail -f 100 /opt/splunkforwarder/var/log/splunk/splunkd.log



######################
btols
######################

btool to check typos in config files - ./splunk btool check 

--debug - shows content of config files and their location
	eg. ./splunk btool inputs list --debug

grep command in linux - used to request a specific results from the btool search
	eg. ./splunk btool inputs list | grep index
	eg. ./splunk btool inputs list --debug | grep monitor

# btool 
	https://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/Splunk/9.0.1/Troubleshooting/Usebtooltotroubleshootconfiguration

#########################
Generating Errors 
Review Splunk messgages  
Troubleshooting method
#########################

1. Typo errors in outputs.conf 
if there is an errors in outputs.conf, the internal logs from the forwarding  nodes will not show in the search head.



2. Internal logs is showing but data from index is not showing.
troubleshoot with tail -f 

dmesg.0

[monitor:///var/log/dmesg.0]
disabled = 0
index = main
sourcetype = messages


###################
change a splunk user to root
########################

/opt/splunkforwarder/etc/splunk-launch.conf
SPLUNK_OS-USER = root